pr_body:
This is a redo of one of my oldest PR here (#160) that I got bored updating for nothing a while ago.
I'm obviously not the only one interested with that:
- #160 ;
- #383 *(explains well why this is useful)* ;
- https://github.com/andrewmichaud/thefuck/commit/a90c80ba534363430cb0ba3cafd2e9a288aa2c7a.

This is a non-breaking change.

Hi there,
In our project we use single model with 2 roles like in this snippet:

```python
    class Address(Model):
        class Options:
            roles = {
                'full': whitelist('street', 'zipcode'),
                'short': whitelist('street')
            }
        zipcode = StringType(required=True)
        street = StringType(required=True)

    class User(Model):
        class Options:
            roles = {
                'full': whitelist('name', 'age', 'address'),
                'short': whitelist('name', 'address')
            }
        name = StringType(required=True)
        age = IntType(required=True)
        address = ModelType(Address, required=True)
```
And I can not understand why there is no validation using some role. 
When role=short I think that validation should be done without exceptions for such json: 
```javascript
 {
        'name': 'Bob',
        'address': {
            'street': 'somewhere in the world'
        }
}
```
Can somebody point me in the right direction If there are any problems with PR

- [x] Remove `mChildUpdateRequestTimer` and reuse `mStateUpdateTimer` for restore children;
- [x] Only one enqueued indirect Child Update Request message for one child (adding one new `kSubTypeMleChildUpdateRequest` for this purpose);
- [x] Keep restoring children until the children are restored successfully or removed due to timeout

@ynasser PR for #4917

I compared all keys, certs and csr's, deleted the ones which didnt get used or which were redundant. 

I thought that the README in the folder is enough and that it doesn't need to be documented in https://certbot.eff.org/docs/contributing.html#testing.
